Package scaledmarkets.dabl.analyzer

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Analyzer  
    AnalyzerFactory
    Defines a type that is able to create instances of the various components that are needed to process DABL input.
    Annotation
    A Node annotations implement this.
    ImportHandler
    Finds the DABL source code for a specified namespace, and then parses and analyzes that source (usually be delegating to a NamespaceProcessor).
    VisibilityChecker  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClientState  
    CompilerState
    Contains the entire state of the compiler when processing an input file.
    Dabl
    Wrapper for analyzer, making it convenient to call and providing options.
    DablAnalyzerFactory
    For creating analysis components that analyze DABL input in a client context.
    DablBaseAdapter
    Add methods for name resolution, symbol table creation and management, and Node annotation.
    DablStandard  
    DeclaredEntry
    Annotation for an Id that is a declaration.
    ExprAnnotation  
    FileImportHandler
    Attempts to read the namespace from the file system, using the env variable "DABL_PATH".
    IdentHandler
    An IdentHandler is attached to enclosing scopes when a symbol is not recognized but might be defined later in an enclosing scope.
    IdRefAnnotation  
    LanguageAnalyzer
    Perform symbol resolution and annotation: Create name scope for namespace and add it to the global scope.
    LanguageCoreAnalyzer
    Language analysis that is shared among the LanguageAnalyzer and the TaskProgramAnalyzer.
    LocalRepoEntry
    A LocalRepoEntry declared a local repository for DABL to create.
    NameScope
    All Axxx classes that define a lexical scope should be annotated with this.
    NameScopeEntry
    A DeclaredEntry that refers to a NameScope.
    NamespaceProcessor
    Parses and analyzes DABL source code.
    PrettyPrint
    Output a hierarchical depication of a SableCC AST.
    PublicVisibilityChecker
    A callback handler for checking if access is allowed to an element.
    SymbolEntry
    A symbol table entry.
    SymbolTable
    A table of the symbol (identifier) declarations made within a given lexical scope of a decl file.
